29/03/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan announced on Monday (March 28th) Turkey is taking over responsibility for humanitarian aid operations at the airport in the Libyan city of Benghazi, which has been the bastion of anti-Gaddafi insurgents.
Turkish sources say the mission was taken over at the rebels' request.
In an interview with the British newspaper The Guardian on Monday, Erdogan said Turkey is prepared to mediate between Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi and the insurgents.
(Zaman - 29/03/11;
Hurriyet, Guardian - 28/03/11)
